List available boot entries:
grubby --info=ALL | grep -E "^index|^kernel|^title"

Or more concisely:
grep -E "^menuentry|^submenu" /boot/grub2/grub.cfg | head -20

Set the next boot to a specific entry (one-time, reverts after):
grub2-reboot <index-or-title>

For example:
grub2-reboot 1

Or by title:
grub2-reboot "CentOS Stream (5.14.0-688.el9.x86_64) 9"

Set the default permanently:
grub2-set-default <index-or-title>

After either command, the change takes effect on the next reboot.


